<h2 id="AIAssistants_usage"><a href="#AIAssistants_top">How to Use AI Assistants</a></h2>
<p>AI assistants can be used to speed up coding and reduce errors. However, it's important to remember that they are tools to assist you, not replace you. Always review the code suggestions provided by AI assistants to ensure they are correct and fit your needs. If the AI assistant makes a mistake, correct it and provide feedback to help it improve.</p>
<h2 id="AIAssistants_instructions"><a href="#AIAssistants_top">Instructions for Developers</a></h2>
<p>Developers working with AI Assistants should adhere to the following guidelines:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Clear Instructions:</strong> Provide clear and detailed instructions to the AI Assistant to get the most accurate results.</li>
    <li><strong>Review Generated Code:</strong> Always review the code generated by the AI Assistant to ensure it meets the project's standards and doesn't introduce any bugs.</li>
    <li><strong>Continuous Learning:</strong> AI Assistants learn from the feedback they receive. If the AI Assistant makes a mistake, correct it and provide feedback to help it improve.</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="AIAssistants_future"><a href="#AIAssistants_top">Future Improvements</a></h2>
<p>Future improvements to AI Assistants may include better understanding of context, improved code generation, and more accurate bug detection. Developers are encouraged to provide feedback to help improve the AI Assistants.</p>